main event: A bright green object about 2 feet in diameter was observed flashing and hitting the ground near Cedar Lake, Wisconsin on November 30, 1962.
interesting points: The object had a 3-foot bright white tail or contrails.
The object was observed at treetop level, then moved towards the ground and flashed when it hit the ground.
The location was the southeast end of Cedar Lake.
The witness was a student from New Richmond, Wisconsin.
sighted object: a bright green object with a 3-foot bright white tail or contrails
witnesses: a student from New Richmond, Wisconsin
